The '''''Journal of Personality and Galactic Psychology''''' was a publication that at one point featured research studies on the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Balosar (species)/Legends|Balosar]] [[Species/Legends|species]]. The studies did not indicate any innate or genetic pathologies unique to the Balosars that would lend support to the stereotyping of members of the species as being spineless, weak-willed, and selfish. Instead, those traits emerged due to the condition of the society on the Balosar's crime- and pollution-riddled [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]], [[Balosar/Legends|Balosar]]. At some point no earlier than [[36 ABY]], the studies published in the publication were mentioned in a [[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species (book)|guide]] to various species of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] that was based on the research notes of [[sentientologist]] [[Mammon Hoole]].<ref name="NEGAS">''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The ''Journal of Personality and Galactic Psychology'' was mentioned in the [[2006]] book ''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'' by [[Ann Margaret Lewis (real person)|Ann Margaret Lewis]] and [[Helen Keier]].<ref name="NEGAS" />

